Combining first and third terms, we get
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">âŸ¨</mo><msub><mtext mathvariant="bold">a</mtext><mi>L</mi></msub><mo separator="true">,</mo><msub><mtext mathvariant="bold">a</mtext><mi>R</mi></msub><mo>âˆ˜</mo><msup><mtext mathvariant="bold">y</mtext><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>â‹…</mo><msup><mtext mathvariant="bold">2</mtext><mi>n</mi></msup><mo stretchy="false">âŸ©</mo><mo>+</mo><mo stretchy="false">âŸ¨</mo><msub><mtext mathvariant="bold">a</mtext><mi>L</mi></msub><mo>âˆ’</mo><msub><mtext mathvariant="bold">a</mtext><mi>R</mi></msub><mo>âˆ’</mo><msup><mtext mathvariant="bold">1</mtext><mi>n</mi></msup><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>â‹…</mo><msup><mtext mathvariant="bold">y</mtext><mi>n</mi></msup><mo stretchy="false">âŸ©</mo><mo separator="true">,</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>â‹…</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 
\langle \textbf{a}_L, \textbf{a}_R \circ \textbf{y}^n + z^2 \cdot \textbf{2}^n \rangle +
\langle \textbf{a}_L - \textbf{a}_R - \textbf{1}^n, z \cdot \textbf{y}^n \rangle, 
= z^2 \cdot a
