Simplifying the above equation into a single inner product relation, we get
<span class="katex-display"><span class="katex"><span class="katex-mathml"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy="false">âŸ¨</mo><msub><mtext mathvariant="bold">a</mtext><mi>L</mi></msub><mo>âˆ’</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>â‹…</mo><msup><mtext mathvariant="bold">1</mtext><mi>n</mi></msup><mo separator="true">,</mo><msup><mover accent="true"><mi>y</mi><mo stretchy="true">â†’</mo></mover><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>âˆ˜</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msub><mtext mathvariant="bold">a</mtext><mi>R</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>â‹…</mo><msup><mtext mathvariant="bold">1</mtext><mi>n</mi></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>â‹…</mo><msup><mtext mathvariant="bold">2</mtext><mi>n</mi></msup><mo stretchy="false">âŸ©</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>â‹…</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>âˆ’</mo><mi>Î¶</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo separator="true">,</mo><mi>z</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo separator="true">,</mo></mrow><annotation encoding="application/x-tex"> 
\langle 
\textbf{a}_L -z \cdot \textbf{1}^n, 
\overrightarrow{y}^n \circ (\textbf{a}_R + z \cdot \textbf{1}^n) + y^{n+1} \cdot \textbf{2}^n  
\rangle
=
y^{n+1} \cdot a - \zeta(y,z),
